    <string-array name="drink_activity_descriptions">
        <item> Because of the high amounts of tannins in red wine, which causes bitterness and complements fatty foods, red wine tastes good with beef.</item>
        <item> Because of the sweeter taste of pork, medium-bodied, light, and fruity red wine tastes good with pork.</item>
        <item> Because of a lower amount of tannins in white wine, white usually pairs well with fish.</item>
        <item> Because of a lower amount of tannins in white wine, white usually pairs well with chicken.</item>
        <item> Because of its bubbles, sparkling is generally paired with shellfish and appetisers. </item>
        <item> It is hard to generalize with rosé, but most rosés pair well with strong food or vegetarian foods.</item>
        <item> Because of the alcohol burn from whiskey, you want fatty foods to mute the burn. So a good pairing for whiskey is beef, or even chocolate. </item>
    </string-array>
